{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Lissajous",
  "description": "Lissajous curve generator — decomposed from the legacy `LissajousGenerator` Rust struct into the curated atom library. The curve math is now visible as the graph itself (the TouchDesigner Pattern → Math → Function → Merge → To-SOP shape) rather than sealed inside a single `generate_lissajous` primitive.\n\nTwo modes share the same render path:\n\n- **Smooth**: the X and Y frequencies are continuously oscillating sines (`a = 2 + 1.5*sin(time*freq_x_rate)`, `b = 3 + 2*sin(time*freq_y_rate)`) producing a slowly morphing closed curve. Phase advances linearly at `time * phase_rate`.\n- **Clip Trigger**: on each clip retrigger the frequencies jump to the next row of a curated 10-row harmonic-ratio table (1:2, 1:3, 2:3, 3:4, …). Phase keeps evolving smoothly.\n\nThe outer-card `clip_trigger` toggle picks between the two via a pair of MuxScalar nodes; the table itself lives inside `node.frequency_ratio`.\n\nPer-axis curve construction:\n  freq → math(Floor)+math(Ceil)+math(Subtract) → (a_lo, a_hi, a_lerp) bracket\n  t = generate_range(0..2π)\n  t_lo = array_math(ScaleOffset, t, scale=a_lo, offset=phase)\n  t_hi = array_math(ScaleOffset, t, scale=a_hi, offset=phase)\n  x = array_math(Mix, sin(t_lo), sin(t_hi), scale=a_lerp)\n\nThis blends between the floor and ceil integer Lissajous curves so non-integer frequencies don't produce non-closing scribbles — instead, they morph smoothly between clean closed shapes. The two axis chains are zipped into `Array<CurvePoint>` by `node.pack_curve_xy` (which folds the legacy `generator_math::PROJ_SCALE = 0.25` screen-fit constant into the output). `node.render_lines` carries the animation + dot rendering + beat-flash from the legacy `LineGeneratorHelper`.\n\nBit-perfect parity with the legacy generator at default params.",
